            <bug_when>2008-08-04 20:24:22 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>Using a skeleton-based application, attempting to log, e.g. this.warn(&quot;hello world&quot;) yields no result because no appender has been included by a default &quot;generator.py source&quot;.  Simply adding the line:

        var appender = qx.log.appender.Native;

to the source causes the appender to be loaded and logging works.  It is not necessary to register the appender; only get it to be loaded.  The default appender should load by default.

Derrell</thetext>
          </long_desc>
